%angular
<head>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<style>
.collapsible {
  background-color: #2e72ae;
  cursor: pointer;
  padding: 18px;
  width: 100%;
  text-align: left;
  outline: none;
  font-size: 18px;
  color:white;
  <!--border : none; -->
}

.active, .collapsible:hover {
  background-color: #555;
  color: white;
  font-weight:bold;
}

.collapsible:after {
  content: '\002B';
  color: black;
  font-weight: bold;
  float: right;
  margin-left: 5px;
}

.active:after {
  content: "\2212";
  color:white;
}
.content {
  padding: 0 18px;
  display: none;
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: #f5f5f5;
  font-size : 18px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Demos</h2>

<button type="button" class="collapsible">Quickstart</button>
<div class="content">
<h4><b>Objectives</b></h4>
<p>The <a href="#/notebook/quickstart">Quickstart notebook</a> runs you through short examples on how to get started with the product quickly.</p>
  <ul>
  <li>Creating Snappy Session</li> 
  <li>Using sparks scala apis </li>
  <li>Defining schema and creating SQL tables</li>
  <li>Creating and inserting Dataset into Data Tables</li>
  <li>Using SnappyData Shell</li>
  <li>Using Java Application (JDBC) to connect to SnappyData cluster</li>
</ul>
</div>
<button type="button" class="collapsible">Performance Benchmark (Locally generated data)</button>
<div class="content">
<h4><b>Objectives</b></h4>
<p>This <a href="#/notebook/performance">performance benchmark notebook</a> showcases the performance of the product over Apache Spark 2.1.1 using a locally generated dataset.</p></li>
</div>
<button type="button" class="collapsible">Performance Benchmark (using dataset hosted on S3)</button>
<div class="content">
<h4><b>Objectives</b></h4>
<p>This <a href="#/notebook/2DKKFJNZR">performance benchmark notebook</a> showcases the performance of the product over Apache Spark 2.1.1 using a dataset hosted on Amazon S3.</p></li>
</div>
<button type="button" class="collapsible">NYC taxi analytics using Approximate Query Processing (AQP)</button>
<div class="content">
<h4><b>Objectives</b></h4>
<ol>
<li> <a href="#/notebook/nyctaxianalytics">NYC taxi analytics notebook</a> uses the AQP engine. 
<li>Execute the query on the exact data noting the time it takes to parse parquet data and execute the query using Spark parallel processing  (LEFT PARAGRAPHS)</li>
<li>Execute the same query using Synopses data engine noting both the accuracy and response time of the answer. (RIGHT PARAGRAPHS)</li>
<li>We illustrate various features: constraining the error in query responses, Automatically swapping the approximate visualized plot with an exact response, projecting error rates as part of the query response and automatic query re-routing to underlying data source when error constraints cannot be satisfied.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<button type="button" class="collapsible">Airline online analytics using Approximate Query Processing (AQP)</button>
<div class="content">
<h4><b>Objective</b></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="#/notebook/airlineanalytics">Airline online analytics notebook</a> uses the AQP engine.</h3>
<li>The U.S. Department of Transportation's (DOT) Bureau of Transportation Statistics (BTS) tracks the on-time performance of domestic flights operated by large air carriers.</li>
<li>Summary information on the number of on-time, delayed, canceled and diverted flights is available for the last 20 years.</li>
<li>In this demo we used the 2009-2015 data set (40 million records) and show simple analytic queries on "exact" as well as "sampled" data.You will be able to compare the response times and be able to inspect the accuracy differences.</li>
</ul>
</div>



<h5><i><b>You can always share your thoughts/questions via  <a href="http://snappydata-slackin.herokuapp.com/" target="_blank">slack</a>, <a href="https://gitter.im/SnappyDataInc/snappydata" target="_blank">Gitter</a>, <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/snappydata" target="_blank">stackoverflow </a>, <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/snappydata-user" target="_blank">google groups</a> or encourage us at <a href="http://www.snappydata.io/community" target="_blank"> http://www.snappydata.io/community </a></b></h5>
<div ng-repeat="n in [].constructor(3) track by $index">
    <br>
</div>
<script>
var coll = document.getElementsByClassName("collapsible");
var i;

for (i = 0; i < coll.length; i++) {
  coll[i].addEventListener("click", function() {
    this.classList.toggle("active");
    var content = this.nextElementSibling;
    if (content.style.display === "block") {
      content.style.display = "none";
    } else {
      content.style.display = "block";
    }
  });
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
